{"id":14881954,"mediaExerciseId":"8c901455-f735-4b76-8f80-f327baeb6c02","exerciseName":"1","chapterName":"26","chapterTitle":"Mergers and Acquisitions","groupId":null,"groupTitle":null,"isPremium":true,"sectionName":"26.1","sectionTitle":"The Legal Forms of Acquisitions","pageNumber":866,"solutions":[{"id":6353858,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"In this exercise, we are asked to define a merger and takeover. In addition, we will also differentiate mergers from other acquisition forms. ","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"## Requirement 1\n\n\n\nA **merger** is the complete takeover of one company by another. The acquiring firm keeps its name and identity while acquiring the acquired firm's assets and liabilities. Following a merger, the acquired firm ceases to function as a separate business entity.","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"Now, let us differentiate the merger from other acquisition forms:\n\nA merger is different from the other acquisition forms since it provides a simple legal transaction that is less expensive than other types of acquisition. The rationale for this is that the companies have agreed to merge their overall operations. There is no need to transfer title to the acquired firm's individual assets to the acquiring company.","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":3},{"columns":[{"text":"## Requirement 2\n**Takeover** refers to the transfer of control of a company from one set of shareholders to another. A takeover occurs when one organization seizes control of another.","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":4}],"rating":0,"solutionUuid":"025b135d-6653-4cc9-ae71-588e2a6480bf","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":4}],"textbook":{"authors":"Bradford D. Jordan, Randolph W. Westerfield, Stephen A. Ross","imageUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/textbook_covers/tmpm0p82b7h","imageThumbnailUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/cache/d1/d3/d1d34d106dd29dd2e71be582412ef59d.jpg","id":34320,"isbn":"9781259918957","isPremium":true,"title":"Fundamentals of Corporate Finance","edition":"12th Edition","verifiedSolutionCount":1217,"shouldBeIndexableForSeo":true,"modified":1665448474394,"active":true,"publisher":"McGraw-Hill Education","mainTextbookIsbn":null,"subjects":{"level1":["Social Science"],"level2":["Economics"],"level3":["Finance"]}},"nextExercises":[{"id":14881955,"exerciseName":"2","page":867,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"f42763ab-e9fa-4dec-a9f9-0f787e1c187f","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-26-exercises-2-f42763ab-e9fa-4dec-a9f9-0f787e1c187f"}],"previousExercises":[{"id":14881940,"exerciseName":"22","page":859,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"73982f2b-e4c1-45aa-a4bd-40f172390c2f","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-26-exercises-22-73982f2b-e4c1-45aa-a4bd-40f172390c2f"},{"id":14881938,"exerciseName":"20","page":858,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"35543c2e-7ee0-4809-b99c-b4abb413d150","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-26-exercises-20-35543c2e-7ee0-4809-b99c-b4abb413d150"}],"_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-26-exercises-1-8c901455-f735-4b76-8f80-f327baeb6c02"}